  "description": "Ingvar Karl Einar Jung (1910-03-09 - Unknown) was a Swedish naval engineer and former professor. He was born in Sithlm to director Torsten J. and Gärda Lyttkens. He was married twice, first to Karin Blomqvist, who died in 1940, and then to Heidi Seeger in 1941. He had four children named Bertil, Birgitta, Ingela, and Gunilla. He completed his matriculation examination in Jönköping in 1928 and graduated from KTH in 1932 with an engineering degree, followed by his PhD in 1936. He has worked for various organizations such as Brown Boveri, Maybach Motors, Schiffbauversuchsanstalt, Penhoét, and British Thomson Houston. He has also served in the navy and has been a contractor for coastal and urban hunters and cruisers. He was also appointed professor of steam technology at KTH in 1943 and later transferred to Göteborg shipyard. He has been a member of the Swedish Technical Association since 1934 and has written a thesis titled Wärmeübergang und Reibungswiderstand bei Gasströmungen in Rohren bei hohen Geschwindigkeiten and articles in various journals."
